column2:
I've tried for many hours, gone through multiple PAGES of Google and Reddit search results. This game still hard crashes my PC causing a hard restart. My PC greatly exceeds the requirements, I don't have any weird overclocking BS going on... I'm just trying to play the fucking game, and I can't recommend parting with your money for this headache and experience. I've spent more time trying to troubleshoot than actually managing to play anything of rust. So far I've hit trees with rocks and my PC just black-screens and reboots. I could set my watch by how predictable this outcome is.... 

TLDR;
If you buy this and the game crashes, just refund it before the refund window expires. you likely won't get the game running in a playable or enjoyable state even if your PC exceeds the recommended specs. If it runs for you, kudos, the code gods or something are happy with you. I have no fucking clue.
